Program: Outlook
Title: Review of the Year 1999
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbqym
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Highlights of the year include interviews with retiring Outlook presenter John Tidmarsh; Dr Alistair Mulcahy who performed open heart surgery in a London pub; South African satirical comedian Pieter-Dirk Uys; Mick and Bridie McGoldrick on the sectarian murder of their son Michael; and Eddie Lenihan an Irish story teller and his fight to save a fairy bush in County Clare. Also, fans in London sing their favourite Abba songs, a horseback ride in Iceland and an extract from Tendi's Diary - an AIDS counsellor in Zimbabwe. Show less